      "content": "A meeting isn't really an option, the migration is pretty automated. The decision is based on the energy footprint of the current architecture vs. the new static ones. Since the static models use a fraction of the wattage, the decommissioning of your instance is basically a done deal. Is there a reason why we'd need to review the details specifically for your node?",
